  "target_response": {
    "text": "Not yet — your log can't confirm or refute that hunch, because the sample is too small to say anything. You've tagged afternoon caffeine on only 4 days in the recent window, and no statistically gated pattern has emerged at that size; anything I read off 4 days would be coin-flip territory dressed up as insight. Two things worth knowing while you collect more. Deep sleep from a wrist sensor is itself an estimate — last night's 62 min of deep is a modeled figure, not a lab measurement — so small day-to-day differences carry limited meaning anyway. And the fix is cheap: keep tagging every afternoon coffee, aiming for roughly 10 tagged days, at which point a real comparison against your untagged days becomes possible. If a pattern does emerge then, it will be a correlation to test, not a verdict.",
